Sec. 163.062. EMPLOYEES. The commission may employ personnel,
including veterinarians, inspectors, stenographers, and clerks, as
necessary to the enforcement of Subchapters A-D of this chapter or
the performance of duties under those subchapters. The commission
may assign to those employees any duty under those subchapters.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1415, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

